\v 12 But they had given the fields and villages around the city to Caleb son of Jephunneh as his possession.
\b
\li1 
\v 13 So to the descendants of Aaron the priest they gave these cities, together with their pasturelands: Hebron, a city of refuge for the manslayer, Libnah,
\v 14 Jattir, Eshtemoa,
\v 15 Holon, Debir,
\v 16 Ain, Juttah, and Beth-shemesh—nine cities from these two tribes, together with their pasturelands.
\b
\pmo 
